<br>
Pity: Sympathy and sorrow aroused by the misfortune or suffering of another. <br>
<br>
ex:  You see someone suffering and you feel bad. but walk on by anyway.<br>
<br>
Compassion: Deep awareness of the suffering of another coupled with the wish to relieve it. <br>
<br>
ex:  You see someone suffering and you feel bad. You want to help them.<br>
<br>
Justice: Conformity to moral rightness in action or attitude; righteousness. <br>
<br>
ex:  You see someone suffering and you feel bad. You want to help them and make it happen.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
What good are pity and compassion alone?  They are useless.  Without Justice, Pity and Compassion are emotions not actions.  <br>
<br>
The confusion comes with determing what is Morally Right.  <br>
<br>
The murderer and the corpse.  Obviously there is an imbalance.  What punishment to the murderer could possibly compensate the corpse?  Does it matter why there was a murder or how it was acted out and planned our just that there was a murder?  I am not for blind justice but complete justice.  If the murdered was a sniper and the corpse was Hitler, is there the same imbalance?<br>
<br>
The US court systems has thousands of books trying to define what is morally right.  The Marquess of Queensbury did it in a briefer fashion. <br>
<br>
<a href="http://www.zyworld.com/enembius/sfc/QueensburyRules.htm">Queensbury</a><br>
<br>
The summary:<br>
-Play fair<br>
-Do not hurt the helpless<br>
-Do not hit a man while he is down<br>
-Don't hit below the waist<br>
<br>
And I agree, the inactive poor and destitute make no effort to improve their situation, deserve nothing.<br>
<br>
The down and out who work to improve should receive some help due to compassion, if not justice, depending in the case.  If they don't we should pitch the old, sick and weak off a cliff when they stop being productive. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fbloodtide14744frm44.showMessage?topicID=10.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fbloodtide14744frm44.showMessage?topicID=11.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fbloodtide14744frm44.threadControl?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fbloodtide14744frm44.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fbloodtide14744frm44.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub41.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="bloodtide14744frm9">GENERAL<option value="bloodtide14744frm12">COUNTER-STRIKE<option value="bloodtide14744frm18">Tales Of The Tide<option value="bloodtide14744frm26">OTHER GAMES<option value="bloodtide14744frm44">THE GREAT DEBATE<option value="bloodtide14744frm7">GUILD HALL<option value="bloodtide14744frm20">GUILD RAIDS<option value="bloodtide14744frm25">INSIDER TRADING<option value="bloodtide14744frm46">YO LFG!<option value="bloodtide14744frm27">THE PLEDGE PROCESS<option value